---
import { site } from "@/config/site";
import SectionHeading from "./SectionHeading.astro";
---

<section id="about" class="py-20 lg:py-28 bg-surface-alt">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <!-- Left column -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-3">
        <SectionHeading label="About" title="A bit about me" />

        <div class="fade-up space-y-5 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            I'm Harsh — a backend engineer based in Ahmedabad, India. I build the systems
            that businesses rely on: APIs that handle thousands of requests, databases that
            keep data consistent, and integrations that just work.
          </p>
          <p>
            My most significant work has been at <strong class="text-text-primary">Betorra</strong>,
            where I architected the backend for a multi-provider gaming platform. I integrated
            1,200+ games across 4 external providers, built idempotent transaction processing,
            and designed the entire API contract layer — all running on AWS.
          </p>
          <p>
            I'm currently working as a Backend Engineer at <strong class="text-text-primary">Betorra</strong>,
            architecting production services for a live gaming platform — handling real-time sessions,
            wallet operations, and multi-provider integrations at scale.
          </p>
          <p>
            What I enjoy most is taking a complex business requirement and translating it into
            clean, maintainable code. Whether it's a REST API, a full-stack application, or an
            AI integration — I focus on building things that are reliable, well-documented, and
            easy to work with.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you're looking for someone who can understand your business needs and build the
            technology to support them, I'd love to chat.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right column: Quick facts -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">
        <div class="fade-up rounded-2xl border border-border bg-white p-6 lg:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6">Quick facts</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { label: "Location", value: site.location },
              { label: "Experience", value: "1+ years in production" },
              { label: "Focus", value: "Backend & Full-Stack" },
              { label: "Stack", value: "NestJS · TypeScript · PostgreSQL" },
              { label: "Currently at", value: "Betorra (Backend Engineer)" },
              { label: "Education", value: "B.E. Computer Engineering" },
            ].map((item) => (
              <div class="flex justify-between items-start gap-4 pb-4 border-b border-border last:border-0 last:pb-0">
                <span class="text-sm text-text-tertiary shrink-0">{item.label}</span>
                <span class="text-sm text-text-primary text-right font-medium">{item.value}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
